  "doc_id": "47394",
  "text": "The exponential convergence of MP in terms of the dictionary's coherence is derived in [CITATION_1] for the case of quasi incoherent dictionaries. That condition is too stringent for signals of practical interest, which are far more compressible when using a highly coherent dictionaries than when using an orthogonal or quasi orthogonal basis. Contrarily, the expression (16) gives a realistic appreciation of the broad range of effective applicability of the SPMP approach. Regardless of the dictionary coherence, SPMP can be an effective low memory implemtation of OMP as long as the least square problem, for the determination of the coefficients in the atomic decomposition of each f q , q = 1, . . . , Q, is not an ill well posed problem.",
